===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|head=[[w:John Langdon Down|Down]] [[syndrome]]}}

# {{lb|en|neurology|chiefly|US}} A medical condition caused by a [[chromosomal]] [[excess]], whereby the [[patient]]s bear a certain [[resemblance]] to the [[mongoloid|Mongoloid]] race, such as a small head and [[tilt]]ed eyelids, and typically have a [[delay]] in [[cognitive]] [[ability]] and [[physical]] [[growth]]. {{defdate|from 1961.}}

====Usage notes====
The condition is known only as {{m|en|Down's syndrome}} in the UK.

